<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}-{2}{y}={16}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{2}{x}+{6}{y}={56}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({4},{8}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}+-{2}{y}={16}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}={16}-{\left(-{2}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{{16}-{\left(-{2}{y}\right)}}}{{8}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}{\left(\frac{{{16}-{\left(-{2}{y}\right)}}}{{8}}\right)}+{6}{y}={56}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\frac{{2}}{{8}}\cdot{\left({16}\right)}-\frac{{2}}{{8}}{\left(-{2}\right)}{y}+{6}{y}={56}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{4}-{\left({0.5}\right)}{y}+{6}{y}={56}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{0.5}{y}+{\left({6}\right)}{y}={56}-{4}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{0.5}{y}+{\left({6}\right)}{y}={52}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left({0.5}+{\left({6}\right)}\right)}{y}={52}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6.5}{y}={52}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=\frac{{52}}{{6.5}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}={8}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}+-{2}{\left({8}\right)}={16}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}+{\left(-{16}\right)}={16}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}={16}-{\left(-{16}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}={32}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{32}}{{8}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}={4}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left({4},{8}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

